# Operator Precedence

Operators are evaluated according to their precedence.

Practical Order

1. Parentheses `()`
2. Unary Operators (`++`, `--`, `!`)
3. Multiplication, Division, Modulus (`*`, `/`, `%`)
4. Addition, Subtraction (`+`, `-`)
5. Relational Operators (`<`, `>`, `<=`, `>=`)
6. Equality Operators (`==`, `!=`)
7. Logical AND (`&&`)
8. Logical OR (`||`)
9. Ternary (`?:`)
10. Assignment (`=`, `+=`, `-=`, ...)

