# DSA Foundation

## O(log n)

Logarithmic Time Complexity

An algorithm with `O(log n)` reduces the problem size significantly after each step, often by half.

Example

Binary Search

Every iteration discards half of the remaining search space.

This makes Binary Search much faster than Linear Search for sorted data.

