# Important Definitions

## Assignment Operator

Assigns a value to a variable.

---

## Relational Operator

Compares two values and returns a boolean result.

---

## Logical Operator

Combines or modifies boolean expressions.

---

## Short-Circuit Evaluation

A behavior where Java skips evaluating the second condition when the final result is already determined.

---

## Ternary Operator

A compact alternative to an `if-else` statement.

---

## O(log n)

A time complexity where the problem size is reduced significantly (often by half) after each step.

